Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSdpTopGroup(25.10)                                    setSdpTopGroup(25.10)

Name
       setSdpTopGroup  -  Specifies the location or the hierarchical path of a
       data path

Syntax
       setSdpTopGroup

       [-help]

       -group <group_name>

       [-force]

       {-location <llx><lly> | -hierPath <path>}

       Specifies the location or the hierarchical path of a data path. If  you
       know where SDP will be placed in the design, use the-location option to
       specify SDP location. The advantage of using setSdpTopGroup is that you
       do  not need to specify the hierarchical path for each member of an SDP
       group.

       Before setting setSdpTopGroup -hierPath, you should have:

              * Imported the design

              * Created the SDP group using createSdpGroup

       Before setting setSdpTopGroup -location, you should have:

              * Imported the design

              * Created the SDP group using createSdpGroup

              * Added members to the SDP group using addSdpGroupMember

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each setSdpTopGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setSdpTopGroup.

       -group <group_name>
              Sets the specified SDP group as the SDP top group.

       -force Indicates  that  the specified location should be set even if it
              is outside the existing core boundary. -force automatically  ad-
              justs the core boundary to accommodate the specified location.

       -location <llx> <lly>
              Specifies the location of the SDP top group.

       -hierPath <path>
              Specifies the hierarchical path of the SDP top group.

Examples
              * The  following command specifies the location of the SDP group
                tdsp_sdpGrp:

                setSdpTopGroup -group tdsp_sdpGrp -location 848.82 586.75

              * The following command sets the hierarchical path for  the  SDP
                group column_GRP5 as /DTMF_INST/EXECUTE_INST. As a result, the
                specified  instance names of all members of this SDP will have
                this hierarchical path.

                setSdpTopGroup -group  column_GRP5  -hierPath  /DTMF_INST/EXE-
                CUTE_INST

